FBIS3-36809 "drsov028_a_94011" FBIS-SOV-94-028 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Feb 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Envoy Views Air Strikes as `Counterproductive' LD1002131094 Lisbon Radio Renascenca in Portuguese to Europe 1130 GMT 10 Feb 94 LD1002131094 Lisbon Radio Renascenca Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] Russia is against the ultimatum given to the Bosnian Serbs, but what will it do if air strikes have to be carried out? Very little has been said publicly. [passage omitted] Aleksandr Petrovich, the Russian ambassador in Lisbon, told us that air strikes could endanger the population and further aggravate the conflict. [Begin Petrovich recording] Air strikes in Bosnia against Serbian positions are not the best solution to the Bosnian problem because this would lead, it appears to me, to an escalation of military operations in Bosnia and would be counterproductive. [end recording]
